result.execSummary:
The defendant Nathan Samuel Albright was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Negligent Operation of Motor Vehicle, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 941.01(1).
  • Bail Jumping-Felony, a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 946.49(1)(b).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: 15CF151,15CM298, 15FO179, 15FO263, 15TR2607, 15TR2608 cases called at 11:29 am. Defendant Nathan Samuel Albright in court with attorney Ben Szilagyi.  Scott C. Blader appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Agreement reached and stated on the record. State will move to amend Count 1 in 15CM298 to a violation of Disorderly Conduct in violation of 947.01(1). Preliminary hearing waived. Court questions defendant regarding waiver -accept waiver, finds probable cause, and enters an order binding the defendant over for trial. Information filed. Attorney Szilagyi confirms receipt, waives formal reading.   Defendant advised of minimum/maximum penalty.  Plea QN reviewed w/Defendant.  Plea colloquy entertained.  Collateral consequences explained. Chapter 950 compliance addressed.  Plea:  No Contest to Counts 1 & 2 of 15CF171. No Contest to Amended Count 1 of 15CM298. Court accepts plea and enters JOC. Court dismisses and reads-in Count 3 & 4 of 15CF151, Counts 2 & 3 of 15CM298, 15FO179, 15FO263, 15TR2607, & 15TR2608. Sentencing argument by DA Blader. Sentencing argument by Attorney Szilagyi. Statment by defendant. Court sentences the defendant to: COUNT 1 of 15CF171 & Count 1 of 15CM298-SWD and places on probation for a period of 2 years. Concurrent to Count 2 of 2015CF151.   COUNT 2 of 15CF171-SWD and places on probation for a period of 3 years. CONDITIONS on COUNT 2 ONLY-200 days WCJ, with Huber, No Good Time Credit. Credit for 75 days served. Court does not object to jail transfer. CONDITIONS ON ALL COUNTS:  The defendant must maintain absolute sobriety, may not be present upon the premises of any bars, and is prohibited from possessing/ingesting any impairing substances that have not been prescribed by a physician. AODA and follow through. Psychological exam and follow through, Employment, Terms of Agent. Costs to be paid within 60 days or payment plan. DNA Sample and Surcharge ordered by the Court.  Defendant advised of right to expunge DNA record through the Department of Justice. Appeal Rights Given. Court states all sentences are concurrent to each other and concurrent to any other sentence.
